{"data":{"markdownRemark":null,"npmPackage":{"name":"gatsby-source-github","description":"A gatsby source plugin to source Github&#39;s GraphQL API for build-time data for Gatsby","keywords":["gatsby","gatsby-plugin","gatsby-source-plugin"],"lastPublisher":{"name":"dschau","avatar":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/9015274323adee38f4536bbf562129ee"},"repository":{"url":"https://github.com/DSchau/gatsby-source-github"},"readme":{"childMarkdownRemark":{"html":"<h1 id=\"gatsby-source-github\"><a href=\"#gatsby-source-github\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>gatsby-source-github</h1>\n<p><a href=\"https://travis-ci.org/DSchau/gatsby-source-github\"><img src=\"https://travis-ci.org/DSchau/gatsby-source-github.svg?branch=master\" alt=\"Build Status\"></a></p>\n<p>Source plugin for pulling in Github data (using its <a href=\"https://developer.github.com/v4/\">GraphQL API</a>) at buildtime for static generation and further GraphQL querying with Gatsby</p>\n<h2 id=\"install\"><a href=\"#install\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Install</h2>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\">\n      <pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">npm</span> <span class=\"token function\">install</span> gatsby-source-github --save-dev</code></pre>\n      </div>\n<h2 id=\"how-to-use\"><a href=\"#how-to-use\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>How to use</h2>\n<p>In your <code class=\"language-text\">gatsby-config.js</code>:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\">\n      <pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\">plugins<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    resolve<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'gatsby-source-github'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    options<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n      headers<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n        Authorization<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token string\">`Bearer YOUR_GITHUB_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// https://help.github.com/articles/creating-a-personal-access-token-for-the-command-line/</span>\n      <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n      queries<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>\n        <span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token string\">`{\n          repository(owner: \"nebraskajs\", name: \"speaker-signup\") {\n            issues(last: 20, states: OPEN) {\n              edges {\n                node {\n                  id\n                  author {\n                    avatarUrl\n                    login\n                    url\n                  }\n                  bodyHTML\n                  title\n                  url\n                }\n              }\n            }\n          }\n        }`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n      <span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre>\n      </div>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">queries</code> is an array of GraphQL queries. The algorithm to generate Gatsby GraphQL nodes is described <a href=\"#the-algorithm\">below</a></p>\n<h2 id=\"how-to-query\"><a href=\"#how-to-query\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>How to query</h2>\n<p>In general, use the <a href=\"https://developer.github.com/v4/\">Github API v4 documentation</a> and in particular, the <a href=\"https://developer.github.com/v4/explorer/\">explorer</a> to craft your queries and refer to the the <a href=\"#the-algorithm\">below algorithm</a> for how to query against these results with Gatsby.</p>\n<h3 id=\"using-variables\"><a href=\"#using-variables\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Using variables</h3>\n<p>Additionally, variables can be used/injectd into the queries. Rather than sending a string in the queries array, send an array like so:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\">\n      <pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>\n  <span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token string\">`query getViewer($first: Int!) {\n    viewer {\n      login\n      name\n      repositories(first:$first) {\n        edges {\n          node {\n            name\n          }\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  }`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> first<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token number\">10</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre>\n      </div>\n<h3 id=\"the-algorithm\"><a href=\"#the-algorithm\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>The algorithm</h3>\n<p>The algorithm is quite simple. Itâ€™ll descend through the tree/returned structure, and if it finds an <code class=\"language-text\">edges</code> key will use the parent of that as the node name. For instance, in the above <code class=\"language-text\">repository</code> example, <code class=\"language-text\">githubIssue</code> will be the node name, and <code class=\"language-text\">allGithubIssues</code> will be the way to query against all nodes. In the <code class=\"language-text\">viewer</code> example the node name will be <code class=\"language-text\">githubViewer</code>.</p>\n<p>All fields in the node that are queried against in the Github GraphQL query are available to be queried with Gatsby. For example, in the <code class=\"language-text\">repository</code> example above, <code class=\"language-text\">id</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">author</code> (and subfields), <code class=\"language-text\">bodyHTML</code>, etc. are available to be queried against.</p>","timeToRead":2}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/packages/gatsby-source-github/","id":"950e8b2c-402b-51f5-93ad-06432e25b234"}}